# Cursor Rules for Video LLM Baseline Evaluation Project

## Project Context
This is a research project evaluating Video Large Language Models (LLMs) for detecting video misinformation, inspired by X/Twitter's Community Notes system.

## Code Style
- Python 3.8+
- Use type hints where beneficial
- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Add docstrings to functions and classes
- Use logging instead of print statements for production code

## Project Structure
- `data/`: All datasets (raw, filtered, videos)
- `scripts/`: Utility scripts
- `notebooks/`: Jupyter notebooks for exploration
- `results/`: Evaluation results and outputs

## Key Files
- `download_filter_community_notes.py`: Main data collection
- `explore_data.py`: Data analysis
- `download_videos.py`: Video download helper
- `test_setup.py`: Environment verification

## Research Focus
- Video content understanding
- Misinformation detection
- AI-generated content identification
- Context provision for viewers

## Data Sources
- X/Twitter Community Notes
- AI-generated video datasets
- Deepfake datasets

## Important Notes
- Respect Twitter's ToS and rate limits
- Handle user data responsibly
- Document all evaluation metrics
- Keep research reproducible

